Dnia =C5=9Broda, 25 czerwca 2014 11:20:50 stef pisze:
> i noticed lots of users pgp-sign their mails to mailing-lists. what e=
xactly
> is the reason/usecase/attackvector you defend against for that? what
> exactly is the reason for doing so on public mailing lists? and why d=
oes it
> make sense to sign irrelevant messages like "+1" or "just kidding" -
> assuming no stego usecase is in play.

I sign my e-mails for the same reasons I undersign them. E-mail is dead=
=2Deasy=20
to forge, so when I have something to say, I sign it in a way to ensure=
 that=20
it's as unforgeable as possible.

I sign *all* my e-mail (and try to encrypt as much as possible, but tha=
t's=20
another thing), even trivial, so that if anybody gets e-mail from me th=
at is=20
*not* signed, they will be more likely to suspect foul play.

=2D-=20
